The paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of MapReduce, which is commonly used for large-scale data processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to databases, distributed computing, data structures, programming languages, and software engineering. Specifically, cs.DB (databases) is the most likely category since the paper discusses applying techniques from parallel DBMSs to MapReduce. cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) are also likely categories since the paper deals with scaling up workloads and optimizing storage formats. cs.PL (programming languages) and cs.SE (software engineering) are less likely but still possible categories since the paper discusses preserving programming APIs and making design choices.
